Achieving efficient layered perovskite solar cells is essential to establish the material platform for investigating the working mechanism. In this study, layered perovskite films with a nominal composition of (BA)2(MA)3Pb4I13 (BA = CH3(CH2)3NH3+; MA = CH3NH3+) were fabricated by hot-casting method. The precursor solutions were prepared by dissolving specific stoichiometric quantities of n-butylammonium iodide (BAI), methylammonium iodide (MAI) and PbI2 in N,N-dimethylformamide (DMF). The X-ray diffraction (XRD) pattern of layered perovskite films is shown in Fig. 1a. Three diffraction peaks at 14.20°, 28.48° and 43.28° were well resolved, which match the diffraction peak positions of (1¯\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
